## Summary

The bug was in the `atan()` method of the Complex class. Mathematically, the inverse tangent function has singularities (poles) at z = i and z = -i, where the function is undefined. The test `testAtanI` expected that `Complex.I.atan()` should return `NaN`, but the original implementation didn't handle this special case.

The fix adds a check in the `atan()` method to explicitly return `NaN` when the input is `i` (Complex.I) or `-i` (Complex.I.negate()). This handles the mathematical singularity correctly and makes the test pass.

